cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about improving the performance of object detection using the Cascade R-CNN framework, which is a popular method in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new feature sharing mechanism, which involves modifying the network architecture, so it could also be categorized as cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the COCO dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia research, so it could also be categorized as cs.MM (Multimedia).
